                            <comment id="103569" author="marceloverdijk" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 07:49:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any chance to backport this 4.0.x line?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="103572" author="snicoll" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 08:05:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Current 4.0.x status is that only critical fixes can be integrated in order to avoid regressions, so it will be only available starting 4.1.x (BTW, this issue is the duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-9897&quot; title=&quot;YamlPropertiesFactoryBean and YamlMapFactoryBean&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-9897&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-9897&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="104525" author="marceloverdijk" created="Tue, 17 Jun 2014 02:45:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As described in &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/4.1.0.BUILD-SNAPSHOT/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/YamlPropertiesFactoryBean.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/4.1.0.BUILD-SNAPSHOT/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/YamlPropertiesFactoryBean.html&lt;/a&gt; it&apos;s easy to have per environment properties.&lt;br/&gt;
In Boot it&apos;s easy to use certain environment by using a profile.&lt;br/&gt;
How should we do that in Spring (without Boot)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="104526" author="marceloverdijk" created="Tue, 17 Jun 2014 02:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Besides that I think it&apos;s good to document it the Spring user guide. Current snapshot docs have no reference to Yaml based configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
